        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 7:31AM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 730 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Siesta Shores, or 8 miles south of Zapata, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Zapata High School, Black Bass, Zapata County Fire Department, Zapata
Middle School, Siesta Shores, Romeo T. Flores Park, Zapata County
Public Library, Zapata--Medina, Medina, and Falcon Mesa.

This includes US Highway 83 between mile markers 766 and 782.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
